   519→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   520→;;; LOOP context and clause structures
   521→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   522→
   523→(defstruct loop-context
   524→  "Complete LOOP parsing and expansion context"
   525→  (name nil :type (or null symbol))           ; NAMED loop name
   526→  (iteration-clauses nil :type list)          ; List of loop-iteration-clause
   527→  (accumulation-clauses nil :type list)       ; List of loop-accumulation-clause
   528→  (termination-clauses nil :type list)        ; List of loop-termination-clause
   529→  (body-clauses nil :type list)               ; DO/conditional clauses
   530→  (initially-forms nil :type list)            ; INITIALLY forms
   531→  (finally-forms nil :type list)              ; FINALLY forms
   532→  (with-bindings nil :type list)              ; ((var init) ...) from WITH
   533→  (result-form nil :type t)                   ; Final return expression
   534→  (gensym-counter 0 :type fixnum))            ; For unique variable generation
   535→
   536→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   537→;;; Iteration clause structures (FOR/AS)
   538→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   539→
   540→(defstruct loop-iteration-clause
   541→  "Base structure for iteration clauses"
   542→  (var nil :type symbol)                      ; Loop variable
   543→  (clause-type nil :type keyword))            ; :arithmetic, :in, :on, :across, :hash-keys, :hash-values, :equals
   544→
   545→(defstruct (loop-iter-arithmetic (:include loop-iteration-clause))
   546→  "FOR var FROM x TO y BY z"
   547→  (from nil :type t)                          ; Start expression
   548→  (to nil :type t)                            ; End expression (inclusive)
   549→  (below nil :type t)                         ; End expression (exclusive)
   550→  (above nil :type t)                         ; End expression (exclusive descending)
   551→  (downto nil :type t)                        ; End expression (inclusive descending)
   552→  (downfrom nil :type t)                      ; Start value for descending
   553→  (upfrom nil :type t)                        ; Start value for ascending
   554→  (by nil :type t))                           ; Step expression (default 1)
   555→
   556→(defstruct (loop-iter-in (:include loop-iteration-clause))
   557→  "FOR var IN list [BY step-fn]"
   558→  (list-form nil :type t)                     ; List expression
   559→  (step-fn nil :type t)                       ; Step function (default #'cdr)
   560→  (list-var nil :type symbol))                ; Generated list variable for iteration
   561→
   562→(defstruct (loop-iter-on (:include loop-iteration-clause))
   563→  "FOR var ON list [BY step-fn]"
   564→  (list-form nil :type t)
   565→  (step-fn nil :type t)
   566→  (list-var nil :type symbol))                ; Generated list variable for iteration
   567→
   568→(defstruct (loop-iter-across (:include loop-iteration-clause))
   569→  "FOR var ACROSS vector"
   570→  (vector-form nil :type t)                   ; Vector expression
   571→  (index-var nil :type symbol)                ; Generated index variable
   572→  (vec-var nil :type symbol))                 ; Generated vector variable
   573→
   574→(defstruct (loop-iter-hash (:include loop-iteration-clause))
   575→  "FOR var BEING THE HASH-KEYS/VALUES OF hash-table"
   576→  (hash-form nil :type t)                     ; Hash table expression
   577→  (value-var nil :type symbol)                ; Optional USING (HASH-VALUE v)
   578→  (key-var nil :type symbol)                  ; Optional USING (HASH-KEY k)
   579→  (mode :keys :type keyword))                 ; :keys or :values
   580→
   581→(defstruct (loop-iter-equals (:include loop-iteration-clause))
   582→  "FOR var = init-form [THEN step-form]"
   583→  (init-form nil :type t)                     ; Initial value
   584→  (then-form nil :type t))                    ; Step expression (nil = no stepping)
   585→
   586→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   587→;;; Accumulation clause structures (COLLECT/SUM/COUNT/etc.)
   588→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   589→
   590→(defstruct loop-accumulation-clause
   591→  "Accumulation clause"
   592→  (type nil :type keyword)                    ; :collect, :sum, :count, :maximize, :minimize, :append, :nconc
   593→  (expr nil :type t)                          ; Expression to accumulate
   594→  (into-var nil :type symbol)                 ; Optional INTO variable
   595→  (acc-var nil :type symbol))                 ; Generated accumulator variable
   596→
   597→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   598→;;; Termination clause structures (WHILE/UNTIL/ALWAYS/etc.)
   599→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   600→
   601→(defstruct loop-termination-clause
   602→  "Termination or boolean aggregation clause"
   603→  (type nil :type keyword)                    ; :while, :until, :always, :never, :thereis, :return
   604→  (expr nil :type t))                         ; Condition or return expression
   605→
   606→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   607→;;; Conditional clause structures (IF/WHEN/UNLESS)
   608→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   609→
   610→(defstruct loop-conditional-clause
   611→  "Conditional execution"
   612→  (type nil :type keyword)                    ; :if, :when, :unless
   613→  (condition nil :type t)                     ; Test expression
   614→  (then-clauses nil :type list)               ; Clauses when true (or false for :unless)
   615→  (else-clauses nil :type list))              ; Optional ELSE clauses
   616→
   617→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   618→;;; LOOP Keyword Recognition (T009)
   619→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   620→
   621→(defparameter *loop-keywords*
   622→  '(for as with initially finally do doing return
   623→    collect collecting sum summing count counting
   624→    maximize maximizing minimize minimizing
   625→    append appending nconc nconcing
   626→    while until always never thereis
   627→    if when unless else end and
   628→    from to below above downto downfrom upfrom by
   629→    in on across being the hash-keys hash-values of using
   630→    into named repeat loop-finish)
   631→  "All recognized LOOP keywords.")
   632→
   633→(defun loop-keyword-p (symbol)
   634→  "Return T if SYMBOL is a LOOP keyword."
   635→  (and (symbolp symbol)
   636→       (member (if (keywordp symbol)
   637→                   (intern (symbol-name symbol) :cl)
   638→                   symbol)
   639→               *loop-keywords*
   640→               :test #'string-equal)))
   641→
   642→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   643→;;; LOOP Gensym Generation (T010)
   644→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   645→
   646→(defun make-loop-gensym (ctx prefix)
   647→  "Generate a unique symbol for LOOP expansion using CTX's counter."
   648→  (let ((counter (loop-context-gensym-counter ctx)))
   649→    (setf (loop-context-gensym-counter ctx) (1+ counter))
   650→    (gensym (format nil "~A-~D-" prefix counter))))
   651→
   652→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   653→;;; LOOP Clause Parser Dispatcher (T008)
   654→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   655→
   656→(defun parse-loop-clauses (clauses ctx)
   657→  "Parse LOOP clauses into structured clause objects in CTX.
   658→   CLAUSES is a list of forms from (loop ...).
   659→   Returns the remaining unparsed clauses (should be nil on success)."
   660→  (loop while clauses do
   661→    (let ((keyword (first clauses)))
   662→      (cond
   663→        ;; Named clause
   664→        ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'named)
   665→         (setf (loop-context-name ctx) (second clauses))
   666→         (setf clauses (cddr clauses)))
   667→
   668→        ;; FOR/AS iteration clauses
   669→        ((or (loop-keyword-eq keyword 'for)
   670→             (loop-keyword-eq keyword 'as))
   671→         (multiple-value-bind (clause rest)
   672→             (parse-for-clause (rest clauses) ctx)
   673→           (push clause (loop-context-iteration-clauses ctx))
   674→           (setf clauses rest)))
   675→
   676→        ;; WITH variable binding
   677→        ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'with)
   678→         (multiple-value-bind (bindings rest)
   679→             (parse-with-clause (rest clauses) ctx)
   680→           (setf (loop-context-with-bindings ctx)
   681→                 (append (loop-context-with-bindings ctx) bindings))
   682→           (setf clauses rest)))
   683→
   684→        ;; Accumulation clauses
   685→        ((member keyword '(collect collecting sum summing count counting
   686→                           maximize maximizing minimize minimizing
   687→                           append appending nconc nconcing)
   688→                 :test #'loop-keyword-eq)
   689→         (multiple-value-bind (clause rest)
   690→             (parse-accumulation-clause keyword (rest clauses) ctx)
   691→           (push clause (loop-context-accumulation-clauses ctx))
   692→           (setf clauses rest)))
   693→
   694→        ;; Termination clauses
   695→        ((member keyword '(while until) :test #'loop-keyword-eq)
   696→         (multiple-value-bind (clause rest)
   697→             (parse-termination-clause keyword (rest clauses) ctx)
   698→           (push clause (loop-context-termination-clauses ctx))
   699→           (setf clauses rest)))
   700→
   701→        ;; Boolean aggregation clauses
   702→        ((member keyword '(always never thereis) :test #'loop-keyword-eq)
   703→         (multiple-value-bind (clause rest)
   704→             (parse-boolean-clause keyword (rest clauses) ctx)
   705→           (push clause (loop-context-termination-clauses ctx))
   706→           (setf clauses rest)))
   707→
   708→        ;; RETURN clause
   709→        ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'return)
   710→         (let ((clause (make-loop-termination-clause
   711→                        :type :return
   712→                        :expr (second clauses))))
   713→           (push clause (loop-context-termination-clauses ctx))
   714→           (setf clauses (cddr clauses))))
   715→
   716→        ;; Conditional clauses
   717→        ((member keyword '(if when unless) :test #'loop-keyword-eq)
   718→         (multiple-value-bind (clause rest)
   719→             (parse-conditional-clause keyword (rest clauses) ctx)
   720→           (push clause (loop-context-body-clauses ctx))
   721→           (setf clauses rest)))
   722→
   723→        ;; DO/DOING clause
   724→        ((or (loop-keyword-eq keyword 'do)
   725→             (loop-keyword-eq keyword 'doing))
   726→         (multiple-value-bind (forms rest)
   727→             (parse-do-forms (rest clauses))
   728→           (dolist (form forms)
   729→             (push form (loop-context-body-clauses ctx)))
   730→           (setf clauses rest)))
   731→
   732→        ;; INITIALLY clause
   733→        ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'initially)
   734→         (multiple-value-bind (forms rest)
   735→             (parse-compound-forms (rest clauses))
   736→           (setf (loop-context-initially-forms ctx)
   737→                 (append (loop-context-initially-forms ctx) forms))
   738→           (setf clauses rest)))
   739→
   740→        ;; FINALLY clause
   741→        ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'finally)
   742→         (multiple-value-bind (forms rest)
   743→             (parse-compound-forms (rest clauses))
   744→           (setf (loop-context-finally-forms ctx)
   745→                 (append (loop-context-finally-forms ctx) forms))
   746→           (setf clauses rest)))
   747→
   748→        ;; Unknown - might be a form for simple loop
   749→        (t
   750→         ;; For simple loop, treat remaining as body
   751→         (push keyword (loop-context-body-clauses ctx))
   752→         (setf clauses (rest clauses))))))
   753→  ;; Reverse collected lists to maintain order
   754→  (setf (loop-context-iteration-clauses ctx)
   755→        (nreverse (loop-context-iteration-clauses ctx)))
   756→  (setf (loop-context-accumulation-clauses ctx)
   757→        (nreverse (loop-context-accumulation-clauses ctx)))
   758→  (setf (loop-context-termination-clauses ctx)
   759→        (nreverse (loop-context-termination-clauses ctx)))
   760→  (setf (loop-context-body-clauses ctx)
   761→        (nreverse (loop-context-body-clauses ctx)))
   762→  ctx)
   763→
   764→(defun loop-keyword-eq (form keyword)
   765→  "Check if FORM is equivalent to LOOP keyword."
   766→  (and (symbolp form)
   767→       (string-equal (symbol-name form) (symbol-name keyword))))
   768→
   769→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   770→;;; LOOP Clause Parsers (Stubs - to be implemented in Phase 3+)
   771→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
   772→
   773→(defun parse-for-clause (clauses ctx)
   774→  "Parse a FOR/AS clause. Returns (values clause remaining-clauses)."
   775→  (declare (ignore ctx))
   776→  (let ((var (first clauses))
   777→        (rest (rest clauses)))
   778→    ;; Determine the type of FOR clause
   779→    (cond
   780→      ;; FOR var FROM ... (arithmetic)
   781→      ((member (first rest) '(from upfrom downfrom to below above downto by)
   782→               :test #'loop-keyword-eq)
   783→       (parse-for-arithmetic var rest))
   784→      ;; FOR var IN list
   785→      ((loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'in)
   786→       (parse-for-in var rest))
   787→      ;; FOR var ON list
   788→      ((loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'on)
   789→       (parse-for-on var rest))
   790→      ;; FOR var ACROSS vector
   791→      ((loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'across)
   792→       (parse-for-across var rest))
   793→      ;; FOR var = expr [THEN step-expr]
   794→      ((loop-keyword-eq (first rest) '=)
   795→       (parse-for-equals var rest))
   796→      ;; FOR var BEING THE HASH-KEYS/HASH-VALUES OF hash-table
   797→      ((loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'being)
   798→       (parse-for-hash var rest))
   799→      ;; Default: treat as = with no THEN
   800→      (t
   801→       (values (make-loop-iter-equals
   802→                :var var
   803→                :clause-type :equals
   804→                :init-form nil
   805→                :then-form nil)
   806→               rest)))))
   807→
   808→(defun parse-for-arithmetic (var clauses)
   809→  "Parse FOR var FROM/TO/BY arithmetic iteration."
   810→  (let ((clause (make-loop-iter-arithmetic
   811→                 :var var
   812→                 :clause-type :arithmetic))
   813→        (rest clauses))
   814→    ;; Parse modifiers
   815→    (loop while (and rest (loop-keyword-p (first rest))) do
   816→      (let ((kw (first rest))
   817→            (val (second rest)))
   818→        (cond
   819→          ((loop-keyword-eq kw 'from)
   820→           (setf (loop-iter-arithmetic-from clause) val)
   821→           (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   822→          ((loop-keyword-eq kw 'upfrom)
   823→           (setf (loop-iter-arithmetic-upfrom clause) val)
   824→           (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   825→          ((loop-keyword-eq kw 'downfrom)
   826→           (setf (loop-iter-arithmetic-downfrom clause) val)
   827→           (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   828→          ((loop-keyword-eq kw 'to)
   829→           (setf (loop-iter-arithmetic-to clause) val)
   830→           (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   831→          ((loop-keyword-eq kw 'below)
   832→           (setf (loop-iter-arithmetic-below clause) val)
   833→           (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   834→          ((loop-keyword-eq kw 'above)
   835→           (setf (loop-iter-arithmetic-above clause) val)
   836→           (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   837→          ((loop-keyword-eq kw 'downto)
   838→           (setf (loop-iter-arithmetic-downto clause) val)
   839→           (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   840→          ((loop-keyword-eq kw 'by)
   841→           (setf (loop-iter-arithmetic-by clause) val)
   842→           (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   843→          (t (return)))))
   844→    (values clause rest)))
   845→
   846→(defun parse-for-in (var clauses)
   847→  "Parse FOR var IN list iteration."
   848→  (let ((list-form (second clauses))
   849→        (rest (cddr clauses))
   850→        (step-fn nil)
   851→        (list-var (gensym "LOOP-LIST-")))
   852→    ;; Check for BY modifier
   853→    (when (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'by)
   854→      (setf step-fn (second rest))
   855→      (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   856→    (values (make-loop-iter-in
   857→             :var var
   858→             :clause-type :in
   859→             :list-form list-form
   860→             :step-fn step-fn
   861→             :list-var list-var)
   862→            rest)))
   863→
   864→(defun parse-for-on (var clauses)
   865→  "Parse FOR var ON list iteration."
   866→  (let ((list-form (second clauses))
   867→        (rest (cddr clauses))
   868→        (step-fn nil)
   869→        (list-var (gensym "LOOP-LIST-")))
   870→    ;; Check for BY modifier
   871→    (when (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'by)
   872→      (setf step-fn (second rest))
   873→      (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   874→    (values (make-loop-iter-on
   875→             :var var
   876→             :clause-type :on
   877→             :list-form list-form
   878→             :step-fn step-fn
   879→             :list-var list-var)
   880→            rest)))
   881→
   882→(defun parse-for-across (var clauses)
   883→  "Parse FOR var ACROSS vector iteration."
   884→  (let ((vector-form (second clauses))
   885→        (rest (cddr clauses)))
   886→    (values (make-loop-iter-across
   887→             :var var
   888→             :clause-type :across
   889→             :vector-form vector-form
   890→             :index-var (gensym "LOOP-IDX-")
   891→             :vec-var (gensym "LOOP-VEC-"))
   892→            rest)))
   893→
   894→(defun parse-for-equals (var clauses)
   895→  "Parse FOR var = expr [THEN step-expr] iteration."
   896→  (let ((init-form (second clauses))
   897→        (rest (cddr clauses))
   898→        (then-form nil))
   899→    ;; Check for THEN modifier
   900→    (when (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'then)
   901→      (setf then-form (second rest))
   902→      (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   903→    (values (make-loop-iter-equals
   904→             :var var
   905→             :clause-type :equals
   906→             :init-form init-form
   907→             :then-form then-form)
   908→            rest)))
   909→
   910→(defun parse-for-hash (var clauses)
   911→  "Parse FOR var BEING THE HASH-KEYS/HASH-VALUES OF hash-table."
   912→  ;; BEING THE HASH-KEYS OF table
   913→  (let* ((rest (rest clauses))  ; skip BEING
   914→         (_ (when (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'the)
   915→              (setf rest (rest rest))))  ; skip THE
   916→         (mode (cond
   917→                 ((loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'hash-keys) :keys)
   918→                 ((loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'hash-values) :values)
   919→                 (t :keys)))
   920→         (rest2 (rest rest)))  ; skip HASH-KEYS/HASH-VALUES
   921→    (declare (ignore _))
   922→    ;; Skip OF or IN
   923→    (when (or (loop-keyword-eq (first rest2) 'of)
   924→              (loop-keyword-eq (first rest2) 'in))
   925→      (setf rest2 (rest rest2)))
   926→    (let ((hash-form (first rest2))
   927→          (final-rest (rest rest2)))
   928→      (values (make-loop-iter-hash
   929→               :var var
   930→               :clause-type (if (eq mode :keys) :hash-keys :hash-values)
   931→               :hash-form hash-form
   932→               :mode mode)
   933→              final-rest))))
   934→
   935→(defun parse-with-clause (clauses ctx)
   936→  "Parse WITH var [= expr] [AND var2 [= expr2] ...]. Returns (values bindings rest)."
   937→  (declare (ignore ctx))
   938→  (let ((bindings nil)
   939→        (rest clauses))
   940→    (loop
   941→      (let ((var (first rest)))
   942→        (setf rest (rest rest))
   943→        (if (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) '=)
   944→            (progn
   945→              (push (list var (second rest)) bindings)
   946→              (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   947→            (push (list var nil) bindings))
   948→        ;; Check for AND - if present, skip it and continue parsing
   949→        (if (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'and)
   950→            (setf rest (rest rest))  ; consume AND keyword
   951→            (return))))  ; no AND, done with WITH clause
   952→    (values (nreverse bindings) rest)))
   953→
   954→(defun parse-accumulation-clause (keyword clauses ctx)
   955→  "Parse COLLECT/SUM/COUNT/etc accumulation clause."
   956→  (declare (ignore ctx))
   957→  (let* ((type (intern (string-upcase
   958→                        (string-right-trim "ING"
   959→                                           (symbol-name keyword)))
   960→                       :keyword))
   961→         (expr (first clauses))
   962→         (rest (rest clauses))
   963→         (into-var nil))
   964→    ;; Check for INTO
   965→    (when (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'into)
   966→      (setf into-var (second rest))
   967→      (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   968→    (values (make-loop-accumulation-clause
   969→             :type type
   970→             :expr expr
   971→             :into-var into-var
   972→             :acc-var (or into-var (gensym "LOOP-ACC-")))
   973→            rest)))
   974→
   975→(defun parse-termination-clause (keyword clauses ctx)
   976→  "Parse WHILE/UNTIL termination clause."
   977→  (declare (ignore ctx))
   978→  (let ((type (if (loop-keyword-eq keyword 'while) :while :until))
   979→        (expr (first clauses)))
   980→    (values (make-loop-termination-clause
   981→             :type type
   982→             :expr expr)
   983→            (rest clauses))))
   984→
   985→(defun parse-boolean-clause (keyword clauses ctx)
   986→  "Parse ALWAYS/NEVER/THEREIS boolean aggregation clause."
   987→  (declare (ignore ctx))
   988→  (let ((type (cond
   989→                ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'always) :always)
   990→                ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'never) :never)
   991→                (t :thereis)))
   992→        (expr (first clauses)))
   993→    (values (make-loop-termination-clause
   994→             :type type
   995→             :expr expr)
   996→            (rest clauses))))
   997→
   998→(defun parse-conditional-clause (keyword clauses ctx)
   999→  "Parse IF/WHEN/UNLESS conditional clause."
  1000→  (declare (ignore ctx))
  1001→  (let* ((type (cond
  1002→                 ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'if) :if)
  1003→                 ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'when) :when)
  1004→                 (t :unless)))
  1005→         (condition (first clauses))
  1006→         (rest (rest clauses))
  1007→         (then-clauses nil)
  1008→         (else-clauses nil))
  1009→    ;; Parse then-clauses until ELSE/END or another major keyword
  1010→    (multiple-value-bind (forms remaining)
  1011→        (parse-conditional-body rest)
  1012→      (setf then-clauses forms)
  1013→      (setf rest remaining))
  1014→    ;; Check for ELSE
  1015→    (when (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'else)
  1016→      (multiple-value-bind (forms remaining)
  1017→          (parse-conditional-body (rest rest))
  1018→        (setf else-clauses forms)
  1019→        (setf rest remaining)))
  1020→    ;; Check for END
  1021→    (when (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'end)
  1022→      (setf rest (rest rest)))
  1023→    (values (make-loop-conditional-clause
  1024→             :type type
  1025→             :condition condition
  1026→             :then-clauses then-clauses
  1027→             :else-clauses else-clauses)
  1028→            rest)))
  1029→
  1030→(defun parse-conditional-body (clauses)
  1031→  "Parse forms in a conditional body until ELSE/END/major keyword.
  1032→   Handles DO/DOING prefix and accumulation keywords as ANSI CL requires."
  1033→  (let ((forms nil)
  1034→        (rest clauses))
  1035→    ;; Check for optional DO/DOING prefix (valid inside conditionals)
  1036→    (when (and rest
  1037→               (symbolp (first rest))
  1038→               (or (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'do)
  1039→                   (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'doing)))
  1040→      (setf rest (rest rest)))  ; skip DO/DOING
  1041→    (loop while rest do
  1042→      (let ((form (first rest)))
  1043→        ;; Stop at ELSE, END, or major clause keywords
  1044→        (when (and (symbolp form)
  1045→                   (or (loop-keyword-eq form 'else)
  1046→                       (loop-keyword-eq form 'end)
  1047→                       (member form '(for as with while until
  1048→                                      always never thereis return
  1049→                                      initially finally
  1050→                                      if when unless named)
  1051→                               :test #'loop-keyword-eq)))
  1052→          (return))
  1053→        ;; Handle AND chaining - may have optional DO/DOING after AND
  1054→        (when (loop-keyword-eq form 'and)
  1055→          (setf rest (rest rest))
  1056→          ;; Skip optional DO/DOING after AND
  1057→          (when (and rest
  1058→                     (symbolp (first rest))
  1059→                     (or (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'do)
  1060→                         (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'doing)))
  1061→            (setf rest (rest rest)))
  1062→          (setf form (first rest)))
  1063→        ;; Handle accumulation keywords specially - they consume an expression
  1064→        (cond
  1065→          ((member form '(collect collecting sum summing count counting
  1066→                          maximize maximizing minimize minimizing
  1067→                          append appending nconc nconcing)
  1068→                   :test #'loop-keyword-eq)
  1069→           ;; Accumulation: form + expr = two tokens
  1070→           (let ((acc-keyword form)
  1071→                 (acc-expr (second rest)))
  1072→             ;; Check for INTO
  1073→             (setf rest (cddr rest))
  1074→             (when (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'into)
  1075→               (setf rest (cddr rest)))  ; skip INTO and var
  1076→             (push (list acc-keyword acc-expr) forms)))
  1077→          (t
  1078→           (push form forms)
  1079→           (setf rest (rest rest))))))
  1080→    (values (nreverse forms) rest)))
  1081→
  1082→(defun parse-do-forms (clauses)
  1083→  "Parse forms after DO/DOING until next keyword."
  1084→  (let ((forms nil)
  1085→        (rest clauses))
  1086→    (loop while rest do
  1087→      (let ((form (first rest)))
  1088→        (when (and (symbolp form) (loop-keyword-p form))
  1089→          (return))
  1090→        (push form forms)
  1091→        (setf rest (rest rest))))
  1092→    (values (nreverse forms) rest)))
  1093→
  1094→(defun parse-compound-forms (clauses)
  1095→  "Parse compound forms (for INITIALLY/FINALLY)."
  1096→  (parse-do-forms clauses))
  1097→
  1098→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1099→;;; LOOP Expander (T011)
  1100→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1101→
  1102→(defun expand-loop (ctx)
  1103→  "Expand parsed LOOP context to tagbody-based code."
  1104→  (let* ((block-name (or (loop-context-name ctx) nil))
  1105→         (loop-start (gensym "LOOP-START-"))
  1106→         (loop-end (gensym "LOOP-END-"))
  1107→         ;; Generate variable bindings
  1108→         (iter-bindings (generate-iteration-bindings ctx))
  1109→         (acc-bindings (generate-accumulator-bindings ctx))
  1110→         (with-bindings (loop-context-with-bindings ctx))
  1111→         (all-bindings (append iter-bindings acc-bindings with-bindings))
  1112→         ;; Generate code sections
  1113→         (termination-tests (generate-termination-tests ctx loop-end))
  1114→         (body-code (generate-body-code ctx))
  1115→         (acc-updates (generate-accumulator-updates ctx))
  1116→         (step-code (generate-iteration-steps ctx))
  1117→         (result-form (generate-result-form ctx)))
  1118→    ;; Build the expansion
  1119→    `(let ,all-bindings
  1120→       (block ,block-name
  1121→         (tagbody
  1122→            ,@(loop-context-initially-forms ctx)
  1123→            ,loop-start
  1124→            ,@termination-tests
  1125→            ,@body-code
  1126→            ,@acc-updates
  1127→            ,@step-code
  1128→            (go ,loop-start)
  1129→            ,loop-end)
  1130→         ,@(loop-context-finally-forms ctx)
  1131→         ,result-form))))
  1132→
  1133→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1134→;;; LOOP Code Generation Helpers
  1135→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1136→
  1137→(defun generate-iteration-bindings (ctx)
  1138→  "Generate bindings for iteration variables."
  1139→  (let ((bindings nil))
  1140→    (dolist (clause (loop-context-iteration-clauses ctx))
  1141→      (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause)))
  1142→        (cond
  1143→          ;; Arithmetic iteration
  1144→          ((loop-iter-arithmetic-p clause)
  1145→           (let ((init (or (loop-iter-arithmetic-from clause)
  1146→                           (loop-iter-arithmetic-upfrom clause)
  1147→                           (loop-iter-arithmetic-downfrom clause)
  1148→                           0)))
  1149→             (push (list var init) bindings)))
  1150→          ;; IN list iteration
  1151→          ((loop-iter-in-p clause)
  1152→           (let ((list-form (loop-iter-in-list-form clause))
  1153→                 (list-var (loop-iter-in-list-var clause)))
  1154→             (push (list list-var list-form) bindings)
  1155→             (push (list var `(car ,list-var)) bindings)))
  1156→          ;; ON list iteration
  1157→          ((loop-iter-on-p clause)
  1158→           (let ((list-form (loop-iter-on-list-form clause))
  1159→                 (list-var (loop-iter-on-list-var clause)))
  1160→             (push (list list-var list-form) bindings)
  1161→             (push (list var list-var) bindings)))
  1162→          ;; ACROSS vector iteration
  1163→          ((loop-iter-across-p clause)
  1164→           (let ((vec-var (loop-iter-across-vec-var clause))
  1165→                 (idx-var (loop-iter-across-index-var clause)))
  1166→             (push (list vec-var (loop-iter-across-vector-form clause)) bindings)
  1167→             (push (list idx-var 0) bindings)
  1168→             (push (list var `(aref ,vec-var ,idx-var)) bindings)))
  1169→          ;; = THEN iteration
  1170→          ((loop-iter-equals-p clause)
  1171→           (push (list var (loop-iter-equals-init-form clause)) bindings)))))
  1172→    (nreverse bindings)))
  1173→
  1174→(defun extract-conditional-accum-types (clause)
  1175→  "Extract accumulation types from a conditional clause's body."
  1176→  (let ((types nil))
  1177→    (labels ((check-form (form)
  1178→               (when (and (listp form) (= 2 (length form))
  1179→                          (member (first form)
  1180→                                  '(collect collecting sum summing count counting
  1181→                                    maximize maximizing minimize minimizing
  1182→                                    append appending nconc nconcing)
  1183→                                  :test #'loop-keyword-eq))
  1184→                 (push (intern (string-upcase
  1185→                                (string-right-trim "ING" (symbol-name (first form))))
  1186→                               :keyword)
  1187→                       types))))
  1188→      (mapc #'check-form (loop-conditional-clause-then-clauses clause))
  1189→      (mapc #'check-form (loop-conditional-clause-else-clauses clause)))
  1190→    types))
  1191→
  1192→(defun generate-accumulator-bindings (ctx)
  1193→  "Generate bindings for accumulator variables.
  1194→   Handles both top-level and conditional accumulations."
  1195→  (let ((bindings nil)
  1196→        (seen-types (make-hash-table :test 'eq))
  1197→        (type-to-var (make-hash-table :test 'eq)))
  1198→    ;; First collect all accumulation types including from conditionals
  1199→    (dolist (clause (loop-context-accumulation-clauses ctx))
  1200→      (let ((type (loop-accumulation-clause-type clause))
  1201→            (acc-var (loop-accumulation-clause-acc-var clause)))
  1202→        (unless (gethash type seen-types)
  1203→          (setf (gethash type seen-types) t)
  1204→          (setf (gethash type type-to-var) acc-var))))
  1205→    ;; Also scan body clauses for conditional accumulations
  1206→    (dolist (clause (loop-context-body-clauses ctx))
  1207→      (when (loop-conditional-clause-p clause)
  1208→        (dolist (type (extract-conditional-accum-types clause))
  1209→          (unless (gethash type seen-types)
  1210→            (setf (gethash type seen-types) t)
  1211→            (setf (gethash type type-to-var) (gensym "LOOP-ACC-"))))))
  1212→    ;; Store the type-to-var map in context for later use
  1213→    (setf (loop-context-result-form ctx) type-to-var)
  1214→    ;; Generate bindings for all seen accumulation types
  1215→    (maphash (lambda (type acc-var)
  1216→               (let ((init (case type
  1217→                             ((:collect :append :nconc) 'nil)
  1218→                             ((:sum :count) 0)
  1219→                             ((:maximize :minimize) 'nil))))
  1220→                 (push (list acc-var init) bindings)
  1221→                 ;; For COLLECT, add tail pointer for efficiency
  1222→                 (when (eq type :collect)
  1223→                   (let ((tail-var (gensym "LOOP-TAIL-")))
  1224→                     (push (list tail-var 'nil) bindings)))))
  1225→             type-to-var)
  1226→    (nreverse bindings)))
  1227→
  1228→(defun generate-termination-tests (ctx loop-end)
  1229→  "Generate termination test code."
  1230→  (let ((tests nil))
  1231→    ;; Add iteration exhaustion tests
  1232→    (dolist (clause (loop-context-iteration-clauses ctx))
  1233→      (cond
  1234→        ;; Arithmetic with TO
  1235→        ((and (loop-iter-arithmetic-p clause)
  1236→              (loop-iter-arithmetic-to clause))
  1237→         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1238→               (to (loop-iter-arithmetic-to clause)))
  1239→           (push `(if (> ,var ,to) (go ,loop-end)) tests)))
  1240→        ;; Arithmetic with BELOW
  1241→        ((and (loop-iter-arithmetic-p clause)
  1242→              (loop-iter-arithmetic-below clause))
  1243→         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1244→               (below (loop-iter-arithmetic-below clause)))
  1245→           (push `(if (>= ,var ,below) (go ,loop-end)) tests)))
  1246→        ;; Arithmetic with DOWNTO
  1247→        ((and (loop-iter-arithmetic-p clause)
  1248→              (loop-iter-arithmetic-downto clause))
  1249→         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1250→               (downto (loop-iter-arithmetic-downto clause)))
  1251→           (push `(if (< ,var ,downto) (go ,loop-end)) tests)))
  1252→        ;; Arithmetic with ABOVE
  1253→        ((and (loop-iter-arithmetic-p clause)
  1254→              (loop-iter-arithmetic-above clause))
  1255→         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1256→               (above (loop-iter-arithmetic-above clause)))
  1257→           (push `(if (<= ,var ,above) (go ,loop-end)) tests)))
  1258→        ;; IN list - terminate when list is exhausted
  1259→        ((loop-iter-in-p clause)
  1260→         (let ((list-var (loop-iter-in-list-var clause)))
  1261→           (push `(if (null ,list-var) (go ,loop-end)) tests)))
  1262→        ;; ON list - terminate when list is exhausted
  1263→        ((loop-iter-on-p clause)
  1264→         (let ((list-var (loop-iter-on-list-var clause)))
  1265→           (push `(if (null ,list-var) (go ,loop-end)) tests)))
  1266→        ;; ACROSS vector - terminate when index reaches length
  1267→        ((loop-iter-across-p clause)
  1268→         (let ((idx-var (loop-iter-across-index-var clause))
  1269→               (vec-var (loop-iter-across-vec-var clause)))
  1270→           (push `(if (>= ,idx-var (length ,vec-var))
  1271→                      (go ,loop-end))
  1272→                 tests)))))
  1273→    ;; Add WHILE/UNTIL termination tests
  1274→    (dolist (clause (loop-context-termination-clauses ctx))
  1275→      (case (loop-termination-clause-type clause)
  1276→        (:while
  1277→         (push `(if (not ,(loop-termination-clause-expr clause))
  1278→                    (go ,loop-end))
  1279→               tests))
  1280→        (:until
  1281→         (push `(if ,(loop-termination-clause-expr clause)
  1282→                    (go ,loop-end))
  1283→               tests))))
  1284→    (nreverse tests)))
  1285→
  1286→(defun generate-body-code (ctx)
  1287→  "Generate body code from DO and conditional clauses."
  1288→  (let ((code nil)
  1289→        ;; Get the type-to-var map stored during accumulator binding generation
  1290→        (acc-var-map (loop-context-result-form ctx)))
  1291→    ;; If acc-var-map is a hash table, use it; otherwise create new
  1292→    (unless (hash-table-p acc-var-map)
  1293→      (setf acc-var-map (make-hash-table :test 'eq)))
  1294→    (dolist (clause (loop-context-body-clauses ctx))
  1295→      (if (loop-conditional-clause-p clause)
  1296→          (push (expand-conditional-clause clause acc-var-map) code)
  1297→          (push clause code)))
  1298→    (nreverse code)))
  1299→
  1300→(defun expand-conditional-form (form acc-var-map)
  1301→  "Expand a single form that may be an accumulation inside a conditional.
  1302→   ACC-VAR-MAP maps accumulation types to their accumulator variables."
  1303→  (if (and (listp form) (= 2 (length form))
  1304→           (member (first form) '(collect collecting sum summing count counting
  1305→                                  maximize maximizing minimize minimizing
  1306→                                  append appending nconc nconcing)
  1307→                   :test #'loop-keyword-eq))
  1308→      ;; This is an accumulation form - expand it
  1309→      (let* ((keyword (first form))
  1310→             (expr (second form))
  1311→             (type (intern (string-upcase
  1312→                            (string-right-trim "ING" (symbol-name keyword)))
  1313→                           :keyword))
  1314→             (acc-var (or (gethash type acc-var-map)
  1315→                          (gensym "LOOP-ACC-"))))
  1316→        ;; Store for later use
  1317→        (setf (gethash type acc-var-map) acc-var)
  1318→        ;; Return the update form
  1319→        (case type
  1320→          (:collect `(setq ,acc-var (nconc ,acc-var (list ,expr))))
  1321→          (:sum `(setq ,acc-var (+ ,acc-var ,expr)))
  1322→          (:count `(when ,expr (setq ,acc-var (+ ,acc-var 1))))
  1323→          (:maximize `(setq ,acc-var (if ,acc-var (max ,acc-var ,expr) ,expr)))
  1324→          (:minimize `(setq ,acc-var (if ,acc-var (min ,acc-var ,expr) ,expr)))
  1325→          (:append `(setq ,acc-var (append ,acc-var ,expr)))
  1326→          (:nconc `(setq ,acc-var (nconc ,acc-var ,expr)))))
  1327→      ;; Not an accumulation - return as-is
  1328→      form))
  1329→
  1330→(defun expand-conditional-clause (clause &optional (acc-var-map nil))
  1331→  "Expand a conditional clause to IF/WHEN/UNLESS form.
  1332→   ACC-VAR-MAP is used to share accumulator variables across clauses."
  1333→  (let ((acc-var-map (or acc-var-map (make-hash-table :test 'eq)))
  1334→        (type (loop-conditional-clause-type clause))
  1335→        (cond-form (loop-conditional-clause-condition clause))
  1336→        (then-forms (loop-conditional-clause-then-clauses clause))
  1337→        (else-forms (loop-conditional-clause-else-clauses clause)))
  1338→    ;; Expand any accumulation forms in then/else clauses
  1339→    (let ((expanded-then (mapcar (lambda (f) (expand-conditional-form f acc-var-map))
  1340→                                 then-forms))
  1341→          (expanded-else (mapcar (lambda (f) (expand-conditional-form f acc-var-map))
  1342→                                 else-forms)))
  1343→      (case type
  1344→        ((:if :when)
  1345→         (if expanded-else
  1346→             `(if ,cond-form
  1347→                  (progn ,@expanded-then)
  1348→                  (progn ,@expanded-else))
  1349→             `(when ,cond-form ,@expanded-then)))
  1350→        (:unless
  1351→         (if expanded-else
  1352→             `(if (not ,cond-form)
  1353→                  (progn ,@expanded-then)
  1354→                  (progn ,@expanded-else))
  1355→             `(unless ,cond-form ,@expanded-then)))))))
  1356→
  1357→(defun generate-accumulator-updates (ctx)
  1358→  "Generate accumulator update code."
  1359→  (let ((updates nil))
  1360→    (dolist (clause (loop-context-accumulation-clauses ctx))
  1361→      (let* ((type (loop-accumulation-clause-type clause))
  1362→             (expr (loop-accumulation-clause-expr clause))
  1363→             (acc-var (loop-accumulation-clause-acc-var clause)))
  1364→        (push
  1365→         (case type
  1366→           (:collect `(setq ,acc-var (nconc ,acc-var (list ,expr))))
  1367→           (:sum `(setq ,acc-var (+ ,acc-var ,expr)))
  1368→           (:count `(when ,expr (setq ,acc-var (+ ,acc-var 1))))
  1369→           (:maximize `(setq ,acc-var (if ,acc-var (max ,acc-var ,expr) ,expr)))
  1370→           (:minimize `(setq ,acc-var (if ,acc-var (min ,acc-var ,expr) ,expr)))
  1371→           (:append `(setq ,acc-var (append ,acc-var ,expr)))
  1372→           (:nconc `(setq ,acc-var (nconc ,acc-var ,expr))))
  1373→         updates)))
  1374→    (nreverse updates)))
  1375→
  1376→(defun generate-iteration-steps (ctx)
  1377→  "Generate iteration stepping code using psetq for parallel stepping."
  1378→  (let ((step-pairs nil))
  1379→    (dolist (clause (loop-context-iteration-clauses ctx))
  1380→      (cond
  1381→        ;; Arithmetic stepping
  1382→        ((loop-iter-arithmetic-p clause)
  1383→         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1384→               (by (or (loop-iter-arithmetic-by clause) 1))
  1385→               (descending (or (loop-iter-arithmetic-downto clause)
  1386→                               (loop-iter-arithmetic-downfrom clause)
  1387→                               (loop-iter-arithmetic-above clause))))
  1388→           (push var step-pairs)
  1389→           (push (if descending
  1390→                     `(- ,var ,by)
  1391→                     `(+ ,var ,by))
  1392→                 step-pairs)))
  1393→        ;; IN list stepping - step the list-var, then update var
  1394→        ((loop-iter-in-p clause)
  1395→         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1396→               (list-var (loop-iter-in-list-var clause))
  1397→               (step-fn (or (loop-iter-in-step-fn clause) 'cdr)))
  1398→           ;; Step the list variable
  1399→           (push list-var step-pairs)
  1400→           (push `(,step-fn ,list-var) step-pairs)
  1401→           ;; Update the loop variable to the new car
  1402→           (push var step-pairs)
  1403→           (push `(car ,list-var) step-pairs)))
  1404→        ;; ON list stepping - step the list-var, var is the same
  1405→        ((loop-iter-on-p clause)
  1406→         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1407→               (list-var (loop-iter-on-list-var clause))
  1408→               (step-fn (or (loop-iter-on-step-fn clause) 'cdr)))
  1409→           ;; Step the list variable
  1410→           (push list-var step-pairs)
  1411→           (push `(,step-fn ,list-var) step-pairs)
  1412→           ;; Update the loop variable (which is the same as list-var content)
  1413→           (push var step-pairs)
  1414→           (push list-var step-pairs)))
  1415→        ;; ACROSS vector stepping
  1416→        ((loop-iter-across-p clause)
  1417→         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1418→               (idx-var (loop-iter-across-index-var clause))
  1419→               (vec-var (loop-iter-across-vec-var clause)))
  1420→           ;; Increment the index
  1421→           (push idx-var step-pairs)
  1422→           (push `(+ ,idx-var 1) step-pairs)
  1423→           ;; Update the loop variable
  1424→           (push var step-pairs)
  1425→           (push `(aref ,vec-var ,idx-var) step-pairs)))
  1426→        ;; = THEN stepping
  1427→        ((and (loop-iter-equals-p clause)
  1428→              (loop-iter-equals-then-form clause))
  1429→         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause)))
  1430→           (push var step-pairs)
  1431→           (push (loop-iter-equals-then-form clause) step-pairs)))))
  1432→    (when step-pairs
  1433→      (list (cons 'psetq (nreverse step-pairs))))))
  1434→
  1435→(defun generate-result-form (ctx)
  1436→  "Generate the result form for the LOOP.
  1437→   Handles both top-level and conditional accumulations."
  1438→  (let ((accumulators (loop-context-accumulation-clauses ctx))
  1439→        (type-to-var (loop-context-result-form ctx)))
  1440→    (cond
  1441→      ;; Has top-level accumulators - use first one
  1442→      (accumulators
  1443→       (loop-accumulation-clause-acc-var (first accumulators)))
  1444→      ;; Check for conditional accumulations in type-to-var map
  1445→      ((and (hash-table-p type-to-var) (> (hash-table-count type-to-var) 0))
  1446→       ;; Return the first accumulator found
  1447→       (block find-acc
  1448→         (maphash (lambda (type acc-var)
  1449→                    (declare (ignore type))
  1450→                    (return-from find-acc acc-var))
  1451→                  type-to-var)
  1452→         'nil))
  1453→      ;; No accumulation -> return NIL
  1454→      (t 'nil))))
  1455→
  1456→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1457→;;; LOOP Macro Expander Factory (T012)
  1458→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1459→
  1460→(defun make-loop-expander ()
  1461→  "Create a macro expander for LOOP."
  1462→  (lambda (form)
  1463→    (let* ((clauses (rest form))
  1464→           (ctx (make-loop-context)))
  1465→      ;; Handle simple infinite loop: (loop body...)
  1466→      (if (and clauses
  1467→               (not (symbolp (first clauses))))
  1468→          ;; Simple loop - just wrap in infinite loop
  1469→          `(block nil
  1470→             (tagbody
  1471→                loop-start
  1472→                ,@clauses
  1473→                (go loop-start)))
  1474→          ;; Extended loop - parse and expand
  1475→          (progn
  1476→            (parse-loop-clauses clauses ctx)
  1477→            (expand-loop ctx))))))
  1478→
  1479→;;; ============================================================
  1480→;;; Typecase Macro Infrastructure (030-typecase-macros)
  1481→;;; ============================================================
  1482→
  1483→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1484→;;; Type Specifier to Predicate Conversion (T004)
  1485→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1486→
  1487→(defun type-specifier-to-predicate (typespec value-sym)
  1488→  "Convert a type specifier to a predicate form.
  1489→   TYPESPEC: Type specifier (symbol or list)
  1490→   VALUE-SYM: Symbol to test
  1491→   Returns: Form that evaluates to T or NIL
  1492→
  1493→   Examples:
  1494→     (type-specifier-to-predicate 'integer 'x) => (integerp x)
  1495→     (type-specifier-to-predicate '(or integer symbol) 'x)
  1496→       => (or (integerp x) (symbolp x))"
  1497→  (cond
  1498→    ;; Atomic type specifiers
  1499→    ((eq typespec 'integer) (list 'integerp value-sym))
  1500→    ((eq typespec 'fixnum) (list 'integerp value-sym))  ; fixnum = integer in Clysm
  1501→    ((eq typespec 'symbol) (list 'symbolp value-sym))
  1502→    ((eq typespec 'cons) (list 'consp value-sym))
  1503→    ((eq typespec 'null) (list 'null value-sym))
  1504→    ((eq typespec 'list) (list 'listp value-sym))
  1505→    ((eq typespec 'number) (list 'numberp value-sym))
  1506→    ((eq typespec 'float) (list 'floatp value-sym))
  1507→    ((eq typespec 'single-float) (list 'floatp value-sym))
  1508→    ((eq typespec 'double-float) (list 'floatp value-sym))
  1509→    ((eq typespec 'ratio) (list 'ratiop value-sym))
  1510→    ((eq typespec 'rational) (list 'rationalp value-sym))
  1511→    ((eq typespec 'real) (list 'realp value-sym))
  1512→    ((eq typespec 'character) (list 'characterp value-sym))
  1513→    ((eq typespec 'function) (list 'functionp value-sym))
  1514→    ((eq typespec 'string) (list 'stringp value-sym))
  1515→    ((eq typespec 'vector) (list 'vectorp value-sym))
  1516→    ((eq typespec 'array) (list 'arrayp value-sym))
  1517→    ((eq typespec 'hash-table) (list 'hash-table-p value-sym))
  1518→    ((eq typespec 'package) (list 'packagep value-sym))
  1519→    ((eq typespec 'stream) (list 'streamp value-sym))
  1520→    ((eq typespec 'keyword) (list 'keywordp value-sym))
  1521→    ((eq typespec 'atom) (list 'atom value-sym))
  1522→    ((eq typespec 't) t)
  1523→    ;; Compound type specifiers
  1524→    ((and (listp typespec) (eq (car typespec) 'or))
  1525→     (cons 'or (mapcar (lambda (ts) (type-specifier-to-predicate ts value-sym))
  1526→                       (cdr typespec))))
  1527→    ((and (listp typespec) (eq (car typespec) 'and))
  1528→     (cons 'and (mapcar (lambda (ts) (type-specifier-to-predicate ts value-sym))
  1529→                        (cdr typespec))))
  1530→    ((and (listp typespec) (eq (car typespec) 'not))
  1531→     (list 'not (type-specifier-to-predicate (cadr typespec) value-sym)))
  1532→    ((and (listp typespec) (eq (car typespec) 'member))
  1533→     (cons 'or (mapcar (lambda (item) (list 'eql value-sym (list 'quote item)))
  1534→                       (cdr typespec))))
  1535→    ((and (listp typespec) (eq (car typespec) 'satisfies))
  1536→     (list 'funcall (list 'function (cadr typespec)) value-sym))
  1537→    ((and (listp typespec) (eq (car typespec) 'eql))
  1538→     (list 'eql value-sym (list 'quote (cadr typespec))))
  1539→    ;; Unknown type - fall back to typep
  1540→    (t (list 'typep value-sym (list 'quote typespec)))))
  1541→
  1542→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1543→;;; Expected Type Construction (T005)
  1544→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1545→
  1546→(defun construct-expected-type (clauses)
  1547→  "Construct expected-type from typecase clauses for type-error.
  1548→   CLAUSES: List of (type-specifier . body-forms)
  1549→   Returns: Type specifier (or type1 type2 ...)
  1550→
  1551→   Example:
  1552→     (construct-expected-type '((integer ...) (symbol ...) (cons ...)))
  1553→       => (or integer symbol cons)"
  1554→  (let ((types nil))
  1555→    (dolist (clause clauses)
  1556→      (let ((type-spec (first clause)))
  1557→        (cond
  1558→          ;; Multiple types in a list: ((type1 type2) body...)
  1559→          ((and (listp type-spec) (not (member (car type-spec) '(or and not member satisfies eql))))
  1560→           (dolist (ts type-spec)
  1561→             (push ts types)))
  1562→          ;; Single type
  1563→          (t
  1564→           (push type-spec types)))))
  1565→    (setf types (nreverse types))
  1566→    (if (= 1 (length types))
  1567→        (first types)
  1568→        (cons 'or types))))
  1569→
  1570→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1571→;;; Exhaustive Clause Validation (T006)
  1572→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1573→
  1574→(defun validate-exhaustive-clauses (clauses macro-name)
  1575→  "Validate that clauses do not contain otherwise/t (for etypecase/ctypecase).
  1576→   CLAUSES: List of clause forms
  1577→   MACRO-NAME: Symbol for error message (etypecase or ctypecase)
  1578→   Signals: error if otherwise or t clause found"
  1579→  (dolist (clause clauses)
  1580→    (let ((type-spec (first clause)))
  1581→      (when (or (eq type-spec 'otherwise)
  1582→                (eq type-spec 't))
  1583→        (error "~A: ~A clause not allowed in ~A"
  1584→               macro-name type-spec macro-name)))))
  1585→
  1586→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1587→;;; Typecase Macro Registration (T007, T008)
  1588→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1589→
  1590→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1591→;;; Typecase Macro Expander (T015-T018)
  1592→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1593→
  1594→(defun make-typecase-expander ()
  1595→  "Create a macro expander for TYPECASE.
  1596→   (typecase keyform (type form...) ... [(otherwise|t form...)])
  1597→   Expands to a let binding the keyform, then nested if/type-predicate tests.
  1598→
  1599→   FR-001: Evaluates keyform once and dispatches based on type
  1600→   FR-002: Expands to nested if forms with predicate tests
  1601→   FR-003: Supports multiple type specifiers per clause ((type1 type2) body)
  1602→   FR-004: Supports otherwise and t as catch-all clause keys
  1603→   FR-005: Returns NIL when no clause matches and no otherwise exists
  1604→   FR-006: Evaluates the keyform exactly once, binding to a gensym"
  1605→  (lambda (form)
  1606→    (let ((keyform (second form))
  1607→          (clauses (cddr form))
  1608→          (key-var (gensym "KEY-")))
  1609→      (labels ((otherwise-clause-p (clause)
  1610→                 (let ((type-spec (first clause)))
  1611→                   (or (eq type-spec 'otherwise)
  1612→                       (eq type-spec 't))))
  1613→               (make-type-test (key-var type-spec)
  1614→                 ;; Handle multiple type specifiers: ((type1 type2) body)
  1615→                 (cond
  1616→                   ;; List of multiple types
  1617→                   ((and (listp type-spec)
  1618→                         (not (member (car type-spec) '(or and not member satisfies eql))))
  1619→                    (if (= 1 (length type-spec))
  1620→                        (type-specifier-to-predicate (first type-spec) key-var)
  1621→                        (cons 'or (mapcar (lambda (ts)
  1622→                                            (type-specifier-to-predicate ts key-var))
  1623→                                          type-spec))))
  1624→                   ;; Single type specifier
  1625→                   (t
  1626→                    (type-specifier-to-predicate type-spec key-var))))
  1627→               (expand-clauses (clauses)
  1628→                 (if (null clauses)
  1629→                     nil  ; FR-005: Return NIL when no match
  1630→                     (let* ((clause (first clauses))
  1631→                            (type-spec (first clause))
  1632→                            (body (rest clause)))
  1633→                       (if (otherwise-clause-p clause)
  1634→                           ;; FR-004: Otherwise/t clause - just execute body
  1635→                           (cons 'progn body)
  1636→                           ;; Normal clause - test and branch
  1637→                           (list 'if
  1638→                                 (make-type-test key-var type-spec)
  1639→                                 (cons 'progn body)
  1640→                                 (expand-clauses (rest clauses))))))))
  1641→        ;; FR-006: Bind keyform to gensym for single evaluation
  1642→        (list 'let (list (list key-var keyform))
  1643→              (expand-clauses clauses))))))
  1644→
  1645→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1646→;;; Etypecase Macro Expander (T027-T031)
  1647→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1648→
  1649→(defun make-etypecase-expander ()
  1650→  "Create a macro expander for ETYPECASE.
  1651→   (etypecase keyform (type form...) ...)
  1652→   Like typecase but signals type-error when no clause matches.
  1653→   Does NOT allow otherwise/t clauses.
  1654→
  1655→   FR-007: Evaluates keyform once and dispatches based on type
  1656→   FR-008: Signals type-error with :datum and :expected-type when no match
  1657→   FR-009: otherwise/t clauses are NOT allowed
  1658→   FR-010: :expected-type is (or type1 type2 ...) of all clause types"
  1659→  (lambda (form)
  1660→    (let ((keyform (second form))
  1661→          (clauses (cddr form))
  1662→          (key-var (gensym "KEY-")))
  1663→      ;; FR-009: Validate no otherwise/t clauses
  1664→      (validate-exhaustive-clauses clauses 'etypecase)
  1665→      (let ((expected-type (construct-expected-type clauses)))
  1666→        (labels ((make-type-test (key-var type-spec)
  1667→                   ;; Handle multiple type specifiers: ((type1 type2) body)
  1668→                   (cond
  1669→                     ;; List of multiple types
  1670→                     ((and (listp type-spec)
  1671→                           (not (member (car type-spec) '(or and not member satisfies eql))))
  1672→                      (if (= 1 (length type-spec))
  1673→                          (type-specifier-to-predicate (first type-spec) key-var)
  1674→                          (cons 'or (mapcar (lambda (ts)
  1675→                                              (type-specifier-to-predicate ts key-var))
  1676→                                            type-spec))))
  1677→                     ;; Single type specifier
  1678→                     (t
  1679→                      (type-specifier-to-predicate type-spec key-var))))
  1680→                 (expand-clauses (clauses)
  1681→                   (if (null clauses)
  1682→                       ;; FR-008: No match - signal type-error
  1683→                       (list 'error 'type-error
  1684→                             :datum key-var
  1685→                             :expected-type (list 'quote expected-type))
  1686→                       (let* ((clause (first clauses))
  1687→                              (type-spec (first clause))
  1688→                              (body (rest clause)))
  1689→                         ;; Normal clause - test and branch
  1690→                         (list 'if
  1691→                               (make-type-test key-var type-spec)
  1692→                               (cons 'progn body)
  1693→                               (expand-clauses (rest clauses)))))))
  1694→          ;; Bind keyform to gensym for single evaluation
  1695→          (list 'let (list (list key-var keyform))
  1696→                (expand-clauses clauses)))))))
  1697→
  1698→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1699→;;; Check-Type Macro Expander (T040-T044)
  1700→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1701→
  1702→(defun make-check-type-expander ()
  1703→  "Create a macro expander for CHECK-TYPE.
  1704→   (check-type place typespec [type-string])
  1705→   Signals type-error with store-value restart if type doesn't match.
  1706→   Loops until type matches (after store-value restart).
  1707→
  1708→   FR-015: Signals type-error with :datum and :expected-type if place is not of typespec
  1709→   FR-016: Returns NIL if type already matches
  1710→   FR-017: Provides store-value restart to set a new value
  1711→   FR-018: Re-validates after store-value restart (loop until correct)
  1712→   FR-019: Optional type-string included in error message"
  1713→  (lambda (form)
  1714→    (let* ((place (second form))
  1715→           (typespec (third form))
  1716→           (type-string (fourth form))
  1717→           (value-var (gensym "VALUE-")))
  1718→      ;; Build the type test predicate using place directly
  1719→      (let ((type-test (type-specifier-to-predicate typespec place)))
  1720→        ;; FR-018: Loop until type matches
  1721→        `(loop
  1722→           ;; Check if type matches
  1723→           (when ,(if (eq type-test t)
  1724→                      t
  1725→                      type-test)
  1726→             (return nil))  ; FR-016: Return NIL if correct
  1727→           ;; FR-015, FR-017: Signal error with store-value restart
  1728→           (restart-case
  1729→               (error 'type-error
  1730→                      :datum ,place
  1731→                      :expected-type ',typespec
  1732→                      ,@(when type-string
  1733→                          (list :format-control type-string)))
  1734→             (store-value (,value-var)
  1735→               :report "Supply a new value."
  1736→               :interactive (lambda () (list (read)))
  1737→               ;; Update the place
  1738→               (setf ,place ,value-var))))))))
  1739→
  1740→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1741→;;; Ctypecase Macro Expander (T053-T057)
  1742→;;; -----------------------------------------------------------
  1743→
  1744→(defun make-ctypecase-expander ()
  1745→  "Create a macro expander for CTYPECASE.
  1746→   (ctypecase keyplace (type form...) ...)
  1747→   Like etypecase but provides store-value restart for correction.
  1748→   Loops until a type matches after store-value.
  1749→   Does NOT allow otherwise/t clauses.
  1750→
  1751→   FR-011: Evaluates place value once per iteration and dispatches based on type
  1752→   FR-012: Signals type-error with :datum and :expected-type when no match
  1753→   FR-013: Provides store-value restart to set a new value and re-dispatch
  1754→   FR-014: otherwise/t clauses are NOT allowed"
  1755→  (lambda (form)
  1756→    (let ((keyplace (second form))
  1757→          (clauses (cddr form))
  1758→          (value-var (gensym "VALUE-")))
  1759→      ;; FR-014: Validate no otherwise/t clauses
  1760→      (validate-exhaustive-clauses clauses 'ctypecase)
  1761→      (let ((expected-type (construct-expected-type clauses)))
  1762→        (labels ((make-type-test (key-var type-spec)
  1763→                   ;; Handle multiple type specifiers: ((type1 type2) body)
  1764→                   (cond
  1765→                     ;; List of multiple types
  1766→                     ((and (listp type-spec)
  1767→                           (not (member (car type-spec) '(or and not member satisfies eql))))
  1768→                      (if (= 1 (length type-spec))
  1769→                          (type-specifier-to-predicate (first type-spec) key-var)
  1770→                          (cons 'or (mapcar (lambda (ts)
  1771→                                              (type-specifier-to-predicate ts key-var))
  1772→                                            type-spec))))
  1773→                     ;; Single type specifier
  1774→                     (t
  1775→                      (type-specifier-to-predicate type-spec key-var))))
  1776→                 (expand-clauses-with-return (clauses)
  1777→                   ;; Build nested if with returns on match
  1778→                   (if (null clauses)
  1779→                       nil
  1780→                       (let* ((clause (first clauses))
  1781→                              (type-spec (first clause))
  1782→                              (body (rest clause)))
  1783→                         (list 'if
  1784→                               (make-type-test keyplace type-spec)
  1785→                               (list 'return (cons 'progn body))
  1786→                               (expand-clauses-with-return (rest clauses)))))))
  1787→          ;; Loop until type matches
  1788→          `(loop
  1789→             ;; Try to match a clause - return if matched
  1790→             ,(expand-clauses-with-return clauses)
  1791→             ;; FR-012, FR-013: No match - signal error with store-value restart
  1792→             (restart-case
  1793→                 (error 'type-error
  1794→                        :datum ,keyplace
  1795→                        :expected-type ',expected-type)
  1796→               (store-value (,value-var)
  1797→                 :report "Supply a new value."
  1798→                 :interactive (lambda () (list (read)))
  1799→                 ;; Update the place and loop to re-dispatch
  1800→                 (setf ,keyplace ,value-var)))))))))
  1801→
  1802→(defun install-typecase-macros (registry)
  1803→  "Install typecase-related macros into REGISTRY.
  1804→   Registers: typecase, etypecase, ctypecase, check-type"
  1805→  ;; Register typecase macro (US1)
  1806→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1807→   registry 'typecase (make-typecase-expander))
  1808→  ;; Register etypecase macro (US2)
  1809→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1810→   registry 'etypecase (make-etypecase-expander))
  1811→  ;; Register check-type macro (US4)
  1812→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1813→   registry 'check-type (make-check-type-expander))
  1814→  ;; Register ctypecase macro (US3)
  1815→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1816→   registry 'ctypecase (make-ctypecase-expander))
  1817→  registry)
  1818→
  1819→;;; ============================================================
  1820→;;; Standard macro installation
  1821→;;; ============================================================
  1822→
  1823→(defun install-setf-macros (registry)
  1824→  "Install setf-related macros into REGISTRY."
  1825→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1826→   registry 'setf (make-setf-expander))
  1827→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1828→   registry 'psetf (make-psetf-expander))
  1829→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1830→   registry 'incf (make-incf-expander))
  1831→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1832→   registry 'decf (make-decf-expander))
  1833→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1834→   registry 'push (make-push-expander))
  1835→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1836→   registry 'pop (make-pop-expander))
  1837→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1838→   registry 'pushnew (make-pushnew-expander))
  1839→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1840→   registry 'rotatef (make-rotatef-expander))
  1841→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1842→   registry 'shiftf (make-shiftf-expander))
  1843→  registry)
  1844→
  1845→(defun install-standard-macros (registry)
  1846→  "Install all standard macros into REGISTRY."
  1847→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1848→   registry 'when (make-when-expander))
  1849→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1850→   registry 'unless (make-unless-expander))
  1851→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1852→   registry 'cond (make-cond-expander))
  1853→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1854→   registry 'case (make-case-expander))
  1855→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1856→   registry 'and (make-and-expander))
  1857→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1858→   registry 'or (make-or-expander))
  1859→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1860→   registry 'prog1 (make-prog1-expander))
  1861→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1862→   registry 'prog2 (make-prog2-expander))
  1863→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1864→   registry 'do (make-do-expander))
  1865→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1866→   registry 'do* (make-do*-expander))
  1867→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1868→   registry 'dolist (make-dolist-expander))
  1869→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1870→   registry 'dotimes (make-dotimes-expander))
  1871→  ;; LOOP macro (029-loop-macro)
  1872→  (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
  1873→   registry 'loop (make-loop-expander))
  1874→  ;; Also install setf-related macros
  1875→  (install-setf-macros registry)
  1876→  ;; Install typecase macros (030-typecase-macros)
  1877→  (install-typecase-macros registry)
